1
00:00:03,604 --> 00:00:07,541
After closing
Sanchi real estate by the sea…

2
00:00:07,608 --> 00:00:09,443
Go right away, go!

3
00:00:09,510 --> 00:00:13,814
…Machi Sangenya came back
to her old job at Teiko Real Estate.

4
00:00:14,315 --> 00:00:16,851
Online criticism
is not worth being scared of.

5
00:00:16,917 --> 00:00:20,287
And she has been selling homes like crazy!

6
00:00:20,354 --> 00:00:23,758
Her genius ways were clear to everyone,

7
00:00:23,824 --> 00:00:28,396
and she seemed
to have momentum on her side.

8
00:00:29,897 --> 00:00:31,198
I'm a realtor.

9
00:00:31,766 --> 00:00:34,101
An opponent trying to drag her down…

10
00:00:34,168 --> 00:00:36,070
You must get rid of it
right here right now!

11
00:00:36,404 --> 00:00:38,939
…was gradually approaching her.

12
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:42,009
You can't go through here today.

13
00:00:44,678 --> 00:00:45,679
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

14
00:00:46,013 --> 00:00:47,281
Starting April,

15
00:00:47,348 --> 00:00:49,383
working environment reform will start.

16
00:00:49,450 --> 00:00:52,420
At our Shinjuku location,
we will review our work hours

17
00:00:52,486 --> 00:00:54,955
as a pre-trial period.

18
00:00:55,022 --> 00:00:57,124
Review? What do they expect to change?

19
00:00:57,691 --> 00:00:59,627
The headquarters informed me

20
00:00:59,693 --> 00:01:02,696
to limit the monthly work hours
to 190 hours.

21
00:01:02,997 --> 00:01:04,465
Not really the headquarters, but the law.

22
00:01:04,532 --> 00:01:06,000
Well, you are right.

23
00:01:06,634 --> 00:01:11,238
Kagimura, what does it mean
when your monthly work hour is 190?

24
00:01:11,305 --> 00:01:13,107
-I don't know.
-Of course, you don't.

25
00:01:13,174 --> 00:01:14,875
-Niwano, explain it.
-Yes.

26
00:01:15,176 --> 00:01:17,411
Say you work eight hours a day,

27
00:01:17,478 --> 00:01:20,214
if you work 20 days a month,
then that's 160 hours of work.

28
00:01:20,281 --> 00:01:22,450
The total monthly work hours are 190,

29
00:01:22,516 --> 00:01:24,185
so that would leave 30 hours for overtime.

30
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:28,355
Then that means one and a half hours
of overtime per day?

31
00:01:28,422 --> 00:01:31,091
What? Working that much overtime
every day is no joke.

32
00:01:31,158 --> 00:01:33,194
For us, it's normal!

33
00:01:33,727 --> 00:01:35,396
This is not happening.

34
00:01:37,698 --> 00:01:41,936
If you feel like your overtime
will exceed 30 hours, report to me.

35
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:44,738
What happens when we report it?

36
00:01:45,406 --> 00:01:48,776
The work that a person couldn't get done
will be given to someone else.

37
00:01:48,843 --> 00:01:52,513
When it's given to someone else,
then wouldn't they have to work overtime?

38
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:55,749
If that's the case,
then I'll think of something else.

39
00:01:55,816 --> 00:01:59,787
Actually, I would like for you
to avoid that situation.

40
00:01:59,854 --> 00:02:03,657
But the headquarters
expect more sales than ever, right?

41
00:02:03,724 --> 00:02:06,794
Less overtime but more sales?
That's a contradiction.

42
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:09,830
Well, so you know…

43
00:02:09,897 --> 00:02:15,336
It means to work more efficiently
than ever before from now.

44
00:02:15,402 --> 00:02:18,439
I will go meet my clients.

45
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:24,912
For now, do not come to work
on your day off.

46
00:02:24,979 --> 00:02:26,080
-Yes!
-Yes!

47
00:02:27,781 --> 00:02:30,918
As for the rest,
we'll think of something together.

48
00:02:30,985 --> 00:02:32,386
It's a trial period, after all.

49
00:02:34,021 --> 00:02:36,524
I worked day and night,

50
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:38,826
so our mortgage was paid off a while back.

51
00:02:40,561 --> 00:02:44,999
We were planning to open a coffee shop
when I retired,

52
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:48,068
but my daughter
who got married last year wants a home,

53
00:02:48,135 --> 00:02:50,070
so I thought I would help her.

54
00:02:50,137 --> 00:02:54,208
First, could I get your budget
and your desired location?

55
00:02:54,742 --> 00:02:58,412
What I can offer is ¥30 million,

56
00:02:58,479 --> 00:03:01,148
and the rest will be financed
by my daughter and her husband,

57
00:03:01,215 --> 00:03:02,783
so about ¥50 million total?

58
00:03:03,551 --> 00:03:07,521
I think it's better for them
to live close to us, so around Koenji?

59
00:03:08,188 --> 00:03:11,125
My daughter doesn't plan ahead at all,
so it makes me anxious.

60
00:03:11,992 --> 00:03:13,627
She says she wants a house,

61
00:03:13,694 --> 00:03:17,164
but has no idea what kind of a house
would be good for her in the future.

62
00:03:17,631 --> 00:03:20,301
I have no idea what her husband
is thinking either.

63
00:03:20,367 --> 00:03:22,303
So since I'm helping them pay for it,

64
00:03:22,369 --> 00:03:26,040
I want to select a few for them
to choose from.

65
00:03:26,473 --> 00:03:27,942
I understand.

66
00:03:28,008 --> 00:03:30,811
I'll get some properties together
and get in touch with you.

67
00:03:31,412 --> 00:03:34,648
There is no house I can't sell!

68
00:03:55,369 --> 00:03:58,005
Because I want to capture
Ms. Sangenya's attention.

69
00:04:02,076 --> 00:04:04,111
-Welcome back.
-Hello.

70
00:04:25,466 --> 00:04:27,568
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

71
00:04:41,382 --> 00:04:42,483
What is this?

72
00:04:42,549 --> 00:04:45,919
They are going to play music
at the end of the work day from now on.

73
00:04:45,986 --> 00:04:48,322
It's nice and clear. It's awesome.

74
00:04:48,389 --> 00:04:50,457
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

75
00:04:50,524 --> 00:04:52,092
Now, whoever can go home now, go.

76
00:04:52,159 --> 00:04:53,661
I'll go home then.

77
00:04:53,727 --> 00:04:55,362
Me too. See you.

78
00:04:55,429 --> 00:04:57,031
-Good work.
-It's the rule.

79
00:04:57,097 --> 00:04:58,365
Goodbye.

80
00:04:58,432 --> 00:05:00,134
-Niwano, let's leave too.
-Yes.

81
00:05:05,172 --> 00:05:08,075
-See you later.
-Goodbye.

82
00:05:08,776 --> 00:05:09,777
Let's go.

83
00:05:09,843 --> 00:05:14,548
I've been feeling bad leaving on time
since Manager and Sanchi came back.

84
00:05:14,615 --> 00:05:16,383
But this work environment reform
is awesome.

85
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:21,422
Yes, but then it's tough
that we can't get that overtime pay.

86
00:05:21,488 --> 00:05:23,757
What? Is your wife waiting for you
at home with your dinner?

87
00:05:23,824 --> 00:05:27,728
Of course! We're newlyweds!

88
00:05:27,795 --> 00:05:30,397
That's so awesome.

89
00:05:36,070 --> 00:05:37,337
Another one.

90
00:05:39,406 --> 00:05:43,110
I am not motivated at all
since no good-looking guys are here.

91
00:05:43,177 --> 00:05:46,513
Shirasu, that's a bit rude.

92
00:05:46,580 --> 00:05:50,684
Niwano is just as good looking
as Adachi and Rusudo.

93
00:05:50,751 --> 00:05:52,152
Really?

94
00:05:52,553 --> 00:05:55,255
Manager, Rusudo is good looking,

95
00:05:55,322 --> 00:05:57,991
but he's weird right?

96
00:05:58,058 --> 00:06:00,260
He knew that Sanchi was homeless too.

97
00:06:00,327 --> 00:06:02,296
What? She was homeless?

98
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:03,931
I'll explain that later.

99
00:06:03,997 --> 00:06:06,967
Maybe he's an ex-boyfriend?

100
00:06:07,901 --> 00:06:09,169
Ex-boyfriend?

101
00:06:09,236 --> 00:06:12,005
No, that's not possible.
That's definitely not possible.

102
00:06:12,072 --> 00:06:13,607
What are you upset about?

103
00:06:13,674 --> 00:06:16,877
Niwano, you still have a thing for Sanchi?

104
00:06:16,944 --> 00:06:18,378
What are you saying?

105
00:06:18,445 --> 00:06:21,715
You are so persistent. You freak!

106
00:06:29,089 --> 00:06:31,425
-Ms. Sangenya.
-What?

107
00:06:32,426 --> 00:06:36,430
Why did you come back
to Teiko Real Estate?

108
00:06:37,197 --> 00:06:40,601
Actually, why don't you work
as a freelancer?

109
00:06:40,667 --> 00:06:43,537
You work like a freelancer
even when you work here.

110
00:06:44,171 --> 00:06:45,572
It's because of love.

111
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:47,207
The company?

112
00:06:48,642 --> 00:06:52,146
I didn't expect an answer like that
from you.

113
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:54,047
It's Manager.

114
00:06:56,517 --> 00:06:58,185
It's because I love Manager.

115
00:07:05,626 --> 00:07:09,696
It's wonderful to work
with the one you love, huh?

116
00:07:12,499 --> 00:07:14,334
I sort of get it.

117
00:07:17,704 --> 00:07:20,374
I'm caught in the middle too.

118
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:24,311
I was called in separately
by the personnel and the sales department,

119
00:07:24,378 --> 00:07:27,648
and one says to decrease overtime
and the other says to increase sales.

120
00:07:27,714 --> 00:07:29,616
That's absurd.

121
00:07:29,683 --> 00:07:31,752
Decrease overtime and increase sales.

122
00:07:31,819 --> 00:07:33,887
That's impossible.
That's definitely impossible.

123
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:36,857
All you have to do is prove
that if overtime is decreased,

124
00:07:36,924 --> 00:07:40,427
then the sales won't increase.

125
00:07:40,494 --> 00:07:42,696
Then the company will give in.

126
00:07:42,763 --> 00:07:47,768
If we work like crazy and increase sales
with less overtime, the company

127
00:07:47,835 --> 00:07:50,037
will demand even more
unreasonable things from us.

128
00:07:50,103 --> 00:07:52,072
Right. He's right!

129
00:07:52,139 --> 00:07:53,240
But,

130
00:07:53,307 --> 00:07:57,878
it's sad to prove that it can't be done.

131
00:07:57,945 --> 00:08:03,750
When Shirasu kept on proving
that she couldn't sell a house,

132
00:08:03,817 --> 00:08:08,455
we gradually started to accept that.

133
00:08:08,522 --> 00:08:12,426
You just have to prove that
what can't be done, can't be done.

134
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:15,162
You say that Mr. Fuse,

135
00:08:15,229 --> 00:08:19,299
but if I wasn't tortured by Sanchi,
then I might have been…

136
00:08:20,834 --> 00:08:23,503
a top sales lady.

137
00:08:24,638 --> 00:08:27,407
Ms. Shirasu, if you keep on lying.
You'll be fired! Fired!

138
00:08:27,474 --> 00:08:29,376
Why would you say that!

139
00:08:29,443 --> 00:08:32,312
Niwano, you are not a newbie anymore,

140
00:08:32,379 --> 00:08:36,149
so train that Kagimura who always says
"Can't" and "I don't know".

141
00:08:37,417 --> 00:08:39,186
No, don't say that.

142
00:08:39,253 --> 00:08:41,488
If overtime is decreased
but the sales have to increase,

143
00:08:41,555 --> 00:08:45,158
then we need to train the useless ones
to become useful.

144
00:08:45,225 --> 00:08:46,226
Yes, I'll do my best.

145
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:50,764
Well, but that Kagimura…

146
00:08:51,431 --> 00:08:53,767
He's like the male version of Shirasu.

147
00:08:53,834 --> 00:08:56,103
I wonder if he could even be trained.

148
00:08:56,169 --> 00:08:59,973
No, he's no good. He really is useless.

149
00:09:01,141 --> 00:09:02,709
He's no good.

150
00:09:03,076 --> 00:09:04,111
Allez.

151
00:09:09,316 --> 00:09:12,552
Thinking that the quality of work
will improve by reducing work hours

152
00:09:12,619 --> 00:09:14,221
is nothing but an illusion.

153
00:09:14,688 --> 00:09:18,225
I might be able to outdo Sanchi
if I work harder,

154
00:09:18,292 --> 00:09:21,561
but at my current company,
I'm not even allowed to work hard.

155
00:09:23,697 --> 00:09:27,234
-Why are you at your current company?
-What?

156
00:09:27,601 --> 00:09:32,472
For example, a painter paints
all day long when they want to,

157
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:35,876
and once a painting is done,
they take a break.

158
00:09:35,943 --> 00:09:39,046
Once they have the urge,
they paint again. That's how they live.

159
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:40,747
But I'm…

160
00:09:40,814 --> 00:09:45,118
But you're an employee,
so you can't do that, right?

161
00:09:47,688 --> 00:09:52,726
I'm a freelance worker since I don't
want to get tired of selling houses.

162
00:09:54,127 --> 00:09:57,664
I work when I want
and rest when I need to.

163
00:09:57,731 --> 00:09:59,032
I play when I play.

164
00:09:59,633 --> 00:10:01,902
I think it's fine to have a realtor
like that too.

165
00:10:04,037 --> 00:10:06,173
Mr. Rusudo, you are amazing.

166
00:10:07,007 --> 00:10:08,442
I told you to call me Kenji.

167
00:10:09,743 --> 00:10:11,411
Kenji, you are amazing.

168
00:10:12,946 --> 00:10:16,783
Satoshi, if you worked freely,
then you'd do better

169
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:18,685
than Ms. Sangenya.

170
00:10:19,353 --> 00:10:20,520
You think so?

171
00:10:22,155 --> 00:10:27,094
Who is Ms. Sangenya's current client?

172
00:10:27,594 --> 00:10:31,298
A young couple buying a house
with financial support from her father.

173
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:37,604
I think Sanchi is focusing on the father
who will be funding the house.

174
00:10:47,848 --> 00:10:51,518
Properties with a stylish entry path
are very popular with the ladies.

175
00:10:52,085 --> 00:10:53,887
Why do you take pictures?

176
00:10:54,321 --> 00:10:56,823
It's easier to explain it
to the clients with a picture.

177
00:10:57,324 --> 00:11:00,894
Pictures make things look bigger,
so doesn't the difference put them off?

178
00:11:03,964 --> 00:11:07,434
Pictures will help persuade the clients
to view the property in person.

179
00:11:08,769 --> 00:11:10,037
Huh?

180
00:11:10,971 --> 00:11:13,740
Niwano, why do you do this job?

181
00:11:14,941 --> 00:11:15,942
What?

182
00:11:18,512 --> 00:11:19,646
That's because…

183
00:11:22,115 --> 00:11:24,951
Selling houses is a wonderful job.

184
00:11:25,552 --> 00:11:26,620
Do you really think so?

185
00:11:27,054 --> 00:11:29,956
I do. For a client,

186
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:32,926
buying a house is one of
their biggest investments in life.

187
00:11:32,993 --> 00:11:34,061
Also,

188
00:11:34,127 --> 00:11:37,164
their life is determined
by what kind of house they live in.

189
00:11:39,266 --> 00:11:43,503
So my job is to help clients
with a big part of their lives.

190
00:11:44,137 --> 00:11:47,307
I think it's a very responsible
and amazing job.

191
00:11:48,175 --> 00:11:50,477
But with such low wages,

192
00:11:50,544 --> 00:11:53,513
you don't even know if you can even
buy your own house in the future.

193
00:11:54,381 --> 00:11:58,418
Isn't it sad to sell houses
to others instead?

194
00:11:59,786 --> 00:12:02,522
Just work hard so you can buy
your own house.

195
00:12:02,989 --> 00:12:04,357
Is that possible?

196
00:12:04,991 --> 00:12:07,060
If you don't try,
then you won't be able to.

197
00:12:08,161 --> 00:12:11,398
A dream starts when you start dreaming.

198
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:14,034
A dream?

199
00:12:14,101 --> 00:12:17,070
I live in a time when I don't even know
the pension I pay now

200
00:12:17,137 --> 00:12:19,906
will be available when I'm older.

201
00:12:20,507 --> 00:12:22,876
The company is not thinking
of their employees at all.

202
00:12:23,477 --> 00:12:25,145
It's obvious when you see Manager Yashiro.

203
00:12:25,812 --> 00:12:28,882
They just use and abuse you,
then throw you away.

204
00:12:29,483 --> 00:12:32,486
That's why I want to quit this job

205
00:12:32,953 --> 00:12:35,021
and do something I want to do.

206
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:37,757
What do you want to do?

207
00:12:38,692 --> 00:12:40,227
Something that's "me".

208
00:12:41,495 --> 00:12:44,998
My job at Teiko Real Estate
is full of stuff I don't like.

209
00:12:46,266 --> 00:12:48,301
It doesn't utilize my potential.

210
00:12:49,002 --> 00:12:51,071
Kei Nishikori and Sota Fujii

211
00:12:51,138 --> 00:12:53,640
are geniuses who stuck
to what they love to do, right?

212
00:12:55,041 --> 00:12:57,210
I think if I work like this,

213
00:12:57,844 --> 00:13:01,047
my great potential will be destroyed.

214
00:13:03,049 --> 00:13:04,718
Your great potential?

215
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,588
Instead of training me,

216
00:13:09,422 --> 00:13:12,225
you should think more
about yourself, Niwano.

217
00:13:13,293 --> 00:13:14,895
Or the company will destroy you.

218
00:13:23,036 --> 00:13:24,538
I'm back.

219
00:13:24,604 --> 00:13:26,339
Welcome back.

220
00:13:26,406 --> 00:13:29,309
Kagimura, how was it? Did he teach you
all about the preliminary visit?

221
00:13:29,376 --> 00:13:31,511
No, he was just taking pictures.

222
00:13:33,446 --> 00:13:36,983
Niwano won't do.
Sangenya needs to train him.

223
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:38,652
I'm sorry. I'm going to the restroom.

224
00:13:41,087 --> 00:13:44,491
The Yamajis are about to come,
so I will go greet them.

225
00:13:44,558 --> 00:13:47,060
-Oh, um, Sangenya.
-Yes.

226
00:13:47,127 --> 00:13:50,263
Could Kagimura join you,
so he could learn?

227
00:13:50,330 --> 00:13:51,765
No, thank you.

228
00:13:51,831 --> 00:13:53,099
Don't say that.

229
00:13:53,633 --> 00:13:55,168
Kagimura, go with her.

230
00:13:55,435 --> 00:13:57,170
What? I just came back, so I'm fine.

231
00:13:57,237 --> 00:13:59,573
You're fine? You don't get to decide that!

232
00:13:59,639 --> 00:14:02,209
I'm the manager
and the manager is me. It's an order!

233
00:14:03,009 --> 00:14:06,313
Tokoshima, when you serve tea
to the guests, take Kagimura too!

234
00:14:06,379 --> 00:14:09,549
No, my hands are full.
Unless I hurry, she'll scold me.

235
00:14:09,616 --> 00:14:13,820
What? Kagimura! Go already!

236
00:14:13,887 --> 00:14:15,355
Seriously, mental breakdown.

237
00:14:15,422 --> 00:14:18,058
You know… Stand up now!

238
00:14:20,694 --> 00:14:21,928
It's hot.

239
00:14:23,196 --> 00:14:25,832
-Your wishes are--
-It's fine! Manager.

240
00:14:25,899 --> 00:14:28,201
I'm Sangenya's boss, Yashiro.

241
00:14:28,702 --> 00:14:30,937
Today, a trainee will be with Sangenya

242
00:14:31,438 --> 00:14:33,840
to learn. Thank you.

243
00:14:33,907 --> 00:14:35,075
Nice to meet you.

244
00:14:35,475 --> 00:14:36,543
Hello.

245
00:14:38,745 --> 00:14:40,013
What?

246
00:14:41,314 --> 00:14:46,019
I have these three properties
to show you per your request.

247
00:14:46,553 --> 00:14:50,690
If you would like a tour,
I will take you there immediately.

248
00:14:52,158 --> 00:14:56,896
This property is a minute walk from
Takanawa Gateway,

249
00:14:56,963 --> 00:15:00,533
the new station for the Yamanote line,
which will open in 2020.

250
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:03,470
It is possible that its value
will increase in the future.

251
00:15:05,939 --> 00:15:09,142
It's a one-bedroom condo
and may be too small once you have kids,

252
00:15:09,209 --> 00:15:13,546
but consider it as an investment
since you can always re-sell it.

253
00:15:13,613 --> 00:15:15,148
I see.

254
00:15:16,316 --> 00:15:19,853
Sir, if you use your ¥30 million
as a down payment,

255
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:23,823
it is possible for the Mitsushimas
to pay the monthly mortgage.

256
00:15:23,890 --> 00:15:25,425
I see.

257
00:15:25,492 --> 00:15:27,127
Right, honey?

258
00:15:27,427 --> 00:15:29,896
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

259
00:15:29,963 --> 00:15:32,866
Hey, Niwano. Are you not feeling well?

260
00:15:33,266 --> 00:15:36,469
-No.
-You were fine before. What is it?

261
00:15:37,537 --> 00:15:43,343
I don't know why I'm working here anymore.

262
00:15:44,077 --> 00:15:46,046
What does this job of selling houses

263
00:15:46,579 --> 00:15:48,948
mean to me?

264
00:15:49,382 --> 00:15:52,652
What's the matter?
I don't quite follow what you're saying.

265
00:15:54,187 --> 00:15:55,355
What's funny?

266
00:15:56,289 --> 00:15:58,291
Kagi probably said something to him.

267
00:16:01,995 --> 00:16:03,930
The biter got bit?

268
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:09,903
A house shows that man's status.

269
00:16:10,904 --> 00:16:14,307
So Kentaro, if you buy a house that's
a little out of your league,

270
00:16:14,374 --> 00:16:16,476
it will motivate you to work even harder.

271
00:16:16,543 --> 00:16:20,947
But I recently rejected a promotion
to be a general manager in India,

272
00:16:21,014 --> 00:16:23,783
so I don't think I'll ever
go up the ranks in my company.

273
00:16:23,850 --> 00:16:25,051
I think so too.

274
00:16:25,418 --> 00:16:26,453
Kentaro.

275
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:29,122
A general manager in India
is a great position!

276
00:16:29,189 --> 00:16:31,624
-Why did you reject it?
-I don't want to go to India!

277
00:16:31,691 --> 00:16:33,093
I didn't ask you, Hana!

278
00:16:33,593 --> 00:16:37,063
Kentaro, you're fine
living your life like this?

279
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:39,733
If you don't aim to get promoted,
what are you working for?

280
00:16:39,799 --> 00:16:42,802
I don't want to get promoted
and have to take responsibility.

281
00:16:42,869 --> 00:16:44,504
-I agree…
-What?

282
00:16:44,571 --> 00:16:46,906
-I'm talking to myself.
-Hey, newbie!

283
00:16:46,973 --> 00:16:48,641
Don't you have
pride that you're responsible

284
00:16:48,708 --> 00:16:49,776
for Teiko's future?

285
00:16:50,110 --> 00:16:51,344
No, I don't.

286
00:16:51,411 --> 00:16:55,048
I don't have any plans of being
responsible for my company's future.

287
00:16:55,682 --> 00:16:58,051
Also… San…

288
00:16:58,351 --> 00:16:59,619
It's Sangenya.

289
00:16:59,686 --> 00:17:03,590
Ms. Sangenya,
all these houses are so lame.

290
00:17:03,656 --> 00:17:07,560
Kentaro and I want to live in cool places
like Toyosu.

291
00:17:07,627 --> 00:17:09,462
I don't need it to have any value.

292
00:17:09,529 --> 00:17:11,564
Ms. Sangenya, please don't listen to them.

293
00:17:11,631 --> 00:17:14,167
I'm the one paying for it.
So I need to be satisfied with it--

294
00:17:14,234 --> 00:17:16,669
Kenta and I will be living in it!

295
00:17:16,736 --> 00:17:18,405
Pick one from here!

296
00:17:18,471 --> 00:17:21,408
I think these three properties
are really good, right?

297
00:17:21,474 --> 00:17:24,144
-I think it's good.
-No, I don't like these!

298
00:17:24,210 --> 00:17:26,479
-Pick one from here!
-No!

299
00:17:26,546 --> 00:17:29,082
Kentaro! Shut Hana up!
You are the husband!

300
00:17:29,149 --> 00:17:31,351
-I can't do that.
-What?

301
00:17:31,418 --> 00:17:34,854
Then I'll look for more properties.

302
00:17:34,921 --> 00:17:39,526
I will find a property
that you will all like.

303
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:45,732
Hana, are you cooking and eating well?
Take this.

304
00:17:46,199 --> 00:17:48,768
I'm going somewhere with Kenta now,
so I can't carry that around.

305
00:17:48,835 --> 00:17:50,203
What? Oh…

306
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:54,808
Ms. Sangenya, please enjoy this
with your co-workers.

307
00:17:55,408 --> 00:17:57,644
Thank you very much.

308
00:17:58,244 --> 00:17:59,245
See you.

309
00:18:00,413 --> 00:18:03,082
Children take their parents' love
for granted.

310
00:18:04,984 --> 00:18:08,254
I will be expecting
more　properties from you.

311
00:18:08,321 --> 00:18:09,923
Understood.

312
00:18:12,892 --> 00:18:15,195
What is this?
Everything has skewers on it.

313
00:18:15,261 --> 00:18:16,830
Is this the trend right now?

314
00:18:16,896 --> 00:18:20,700
It's finger food that can be eaten
without chopsticks or a fork.

315
00:18:22,168 --> 00:18:23,803
Finger food?

316
00:18:23,870 --> 00:18:27,040
Go ahead. It's a gift from Mrs. Yamaji.

317
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:28,541
Thank you.

318
00:18:28,608 --> 00:18:30,109
It's also called a pinchos too.

319
00:18:30,176 --> 00:18:31,211
What is that?

320
00:18:31,277 --> 00:18:33,546
It refers to a bite-sized snack.

321
00:18:33,813 --> 00:18:35,215
That looks good.

322
00:18:36,583 --> 00:18:38,751
Well, I guess young ones
don't know much manners.

323
00:18:38,818 --> 00:18:40,220
At least say "thank you" first.

324
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:42,689
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

325
00:18:42,755 --> 00:18:44,891
-We should enjoy it too.
-Yes.

326
00:18:44,958 --> 00:18:46,759
-Let's eat.
-Yum!

327
00:18:47,494 --> 00:18:48,595
Niwano.

328
00:18:52,065 --> 00:18:53,433
How about you Sangenya? Want some?

329
00:18:53,933 --> 00:18:55,702
I'm thinking right now.

330
00:18:55,768 --> 00:18:57,570
I can't eat and think at the same time.

331
00:18:57,871 --> 00:18:59,138
I see.

332
00:18:59,873 --> 00:19:01,674
Well then, I'll have it.

333
00:19:09,082 --> 00:19:12,819
Ms. Shirasu, why did you quit
Teiko Real Estate?

334
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:16,756
I won't tell you.
Because you're a bit weird, Rusudo!

335
00:19:18,324 --> 00:19:20,093
Am I weird?

336
00:19:22,295 --> 00:19:23,596
I guess I am weird.

337
00:19:23,663 --> 00:19:26,966
-You are very weird, very!
-Very?

338
00:19:27,033 --> 00:19:28,568
Very!

339
00:19:28,635 --> 00:19:31,037
You are spying on Sanchi for something,
aren't you?

340
00:19:31,804 --> 00:19:34,173
Spying?

341
00:19:35,642 --> 00:19:38,177
I just respect Ms. Sangenya.

342
00:19:38,678 --> 00:19:40,313
No, you are fishing for something.

343
00:19:40,747 --> 00:19:43,149
You may think I'm stupid,

344
00:19:43,216 --> 00:19:45,985
but even I can tell that.

345
00:19:46,052 --> 00:19:47,754
I never said you are stupid.

346
00:19:49,255 --> 00:19:50,523
I don't think you are stupid.

347
00:19:51,724 --> 00:19:54,794
Really? Then you think I'm smart?

348
00:19:55,595 --> 00:19:56,996
I do.

349
00:19:57,063 --> 00:19:59,165
Then I'll say it…

350
00:19:59,933 --> 00:20:02,502
I used to be the top sales lady

351
00:20:02,569 --> 00:20:06,039
at Teiko Real Estate's Shinjuku office.

352
00:20:06,406 --> 00:20:07,874
Really.

353
00:20:07,941 --> 00:20:11,110
I got awarded several times
by the headquarters.

354
00:20:12,645 --> 00:20:14,747
Ever since Sanchi came,

355
00:20:16,316 --> 00:20:19,419
she picked on me behind everyone's back.

356
00:20:19,852 --> 00:20:21,120
Like how?

357
00:20:21,187 --> 00:20:23,556
I can't remember them now.

358
00:20:23,623 --> 00:20:25,058
I see.

359
00:20:25,792 --> 00:20:27,193
So that's why

360
00:20:28,861 --> 00:20:30,697
I had a nervous breakdown.

361
00:20:31,364 --> 00:20:35,268
Manager and everyone else
turned against me

362
00:20:35,602 --> 00:20:37,670
and sided with Sanchi.

363
00:20:38,338 --> 00:20:41,441
I was all alone.

364
00:20:41,507 --> 00:20:43,109
That must have been hard for you.

365
00:20:44,844 --> 00:20:47,046
You can't tell anybody about this.

366
00:20:47,347 --> 00:20:50,583
You can't tell the owner here
or the other Teiko realtors!

367
00:20:52,719 --> 00:20:56,155
Mr. Rusudo, you are weird, but kind.

368
00:20:56,222 --> 00:20:57,724
Oh, I need to go now.

369
00:20:58,358 --> 00:21:01,628
Thank you. Your coffee is ¥350.

370
00:21:08,901 --> 00:21:09,902
Oh?

371
00:21:12,171 --> 00:21:13,306
Oh, pull it.

372
00:21:16,509 --> 00:21:17,577
Thank you.

373
00:21:20,046 --> 00:21:23,483
He's weird but attractive!

374
00:21:56,416 --> 00:21:57,884
Are you going there again?

375
00:21:57,950 --> 00:21:59,919
Oh, my wife is--

376
00:22:05,658 --> 00:22:08,194
What are you working on right now, Adachi?

377
00:22:08,261 --> 00:22:09,662
I'm preparing paperwork for a contract.

378
00:22:10,096 --> 00:22:11,964
Do you need to do that today?

379
00:22:17,170 --> 00:22:19,372
I don't want you to take this
the wrong way,

380
00:22:20,039 --> 00:22:22,575
but I want to work harder
and sell more houses.

381
00:22:23,242 --> 00:22:25,511
I want my clients to be happy,

382
00:22:25,578 --> 00:22:27,613
and I want to work harder to achieve that.

383
00:22:28,848 --> 00:22:31,284
Those who want to leave can leave,

384
00:22:31,884 --> 00:22:34,587
but I don't think it's right
to prevent other people

385
00:22:35,321 --> 00:22:37,090
from trying to work hard.

386
00:22:45,998 --> 00:22:49,268
Well, shall we drink and talk
about that too?

387
00:22:53,639 --> 00:22:55,608
ADACHI, SANGENYA

388
00:22:59,545 --> 00:23:02,181
Satoshi! Where are you?

389
00:23:02,248 --> 00:23:03,683
I want a game with you.

390
00:23:05,985 --> 00:23:07,153
Manager!

391
00:23:07,653 --> 00:23:10,356
I have to be somewhere now. See you later!

392
00:23:22,235 --> 00:23:23,436
You are hesitating.

393
00:23:25,004 --> 00:23:26,005
I'm talking about you.

394
00:23:28,775 --> 00:23:30,676
Satoshi, you really are cute.

395
00:23:32,278 --> 00:23:34,547
Your hesitation is obvious in your point.

396
00:23:38,885 --> 00:23:42,622
Satoshi Adachi makes a sound argument.

397
00:23:42,688 --> 00:23:45,992
He has a valid point. I know that.

398
00:23:46,492 --> 00:23:51,063
I know that, but even I try
to speak logically with the headquarters…

399
00:23:52,765 --> 00:23:56,869
The headquarters
can't go against the law either.

400
00:23:56,936 --> 00:23:58,604
You are right.

401
00:23:58,671 --> 00:24:04,110
So that's why I don't know what to do now.

402
00:24:05,978 --> 00:24:07,280
Kokoro!

403
00:24:07,847 --> 00:24:09,282
What should I do?

404
00:24:09,348 --> 00:24:12,251
I don't know what you should do,

405
00:24:12,318 --> 00:24:14,987
but I can cast a spell
that will make you feel better!

406
00:24:16,088 --> 00:24:18,558
Yes! Please do!

407
00:24:19,358 --> 00:24:21,427
-I'm going to do it.
-Yes!

408
00:24:21,494 --> 00:24:25,031
Please let Yashiro's worry go away.

409
00:24:25,698 --> 00:24:28,367
Please let him be an energetic Manager.

410
00:24:28,434 --> 00:24:30,636
Chichin pui-pui,

411
00:24:30,703 --> 00:24:34,674
pui, pui, pui!

412
00:24:37,677 --> 00:24:38,945
That works.

413
00:24:42,415 --> 00:24:43,616
-Excuse me.
-Yes.

414
00:24:43,683 --> 00:24:44,951
Can I have another beer?

415
00:24:45,017 --> 00:24:46,385
Yes.

416
00:24:46,452 --> 00:24:48,354
-Newbie?
-Oh?

417
00:24:48,888 --> 00:24:50,056
What?

418
00:24:50,122 --> 00:24:52,291
He doesn't remember his clients.

419
00:24:52,358 --> 00:24:54,594
-He's a bad newbie.
-Let him be.

420
00:24:54,894 --> 00:24:57,230
Excuse me. Could I have a cocktail 830?

421
00:24:57,296 --> 00:24:59,365
-I'll have 830 too.
-Yes.

422
00:25:00,333 --> 00:25:04,403
Oh, they are Sanchi's clients
that I served tea to today.

423
00:25:04,470 --> 00:25:06,806
Ah! Your father is going to buy
a property for you.

424
00:25:06,873 --> 00:25:10,309
Newbie, the properties I saw today
were totally not cool.

425
00:25:10,376 --> 00:25:11,944
Can you find me a stylish house?

426
00:25:12,612 --> 00:25:13,779
In the Bay Area?

427
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:15,915
Right! In the Bay Area!

428
00:25:15,982 --> 00:25:18,150
-Don't you think the Bay Area is nice?
-Huh?

429
00:25:18,784 --> 00:25:21,087
Dad will pay ¥30 million.

430
00:25:21,153 --> 00:25:23,389
The rest we can finance.

431
00:25:26,459 --> 00:25:30,062
Is your budget about ¥45 million?
There are some properties.

432
00:25:31,464 --> 00:25:33,633
-How about this one?
-That's cool!

433
00:25:33,699 --> 00:25:34,967
Like this one.

434
00:25:35,034 --> 00:25:39,205
Now we're talking! Kenta!
I definitely like this one!

435
00:25:40,573 --> 00:25:42,875
-Do you want a tour tomorrow?
-We do!

436
00:25:43,843 --> 00:25:45,278
What time would you like?

437
00:25:45,344 --> 00:25:46,512
Kenta, what time is good?

438
00:25:47,113 --> 00:25:49,048
I want to see it before work, so 9:30?

439
00:25:49,582 --> 00:25:52,685
Then I'll have it ready,
so you can take a look at it.

440
00:25:52,752 --> 00:25:54,320
Yay!

441
00:25:54,387 --> 00:25:55,855
Good job, Kagi.

442
00:25:55,922 --> 00:25:57,390
Well, shall we go now?

443
00:25:58,024 --> 00:26:00,493
-See you.
-See you.

444
00:26:00,559 --> 00:26:03,095
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

445
00:26:03,629 --> 00:26:06,599
-Could I get cocktail 830?
-Yes.

446
00:26:10,269 --> 00:26:11,904
It's the best, isn't it?

447
00:26:12,571 --> 00:26:14,006
Cocktail 830.

448
00:26:14,874 --> 00:26:16,142
You like it too?

449
00:26:19,845 --> 00:26:21,614
Oh, there it is.

450
00:26:22,381 --> 00:26:23,616
I'm so relieved.

451
00:26:28,754 --> 00:26:30,156
In the olden days…

452
00:26:30,890 --> 00:26:33,025
everyone would still be working
at this time.

453
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:35,828
We would help each other,

454
00:26:36,262 --> 00:26:37,730
and prepare for the next day.

455
00:26:39,532 --> 00:26:44,103
When it was done, someone would say,
"All right, let's go out for a drink!"

456
00:26:45,338 --> 00:26:47,506
Then that one drink became two drinks.

457
00:26:49,575 --> 00:26:50,910
Oh, it brings back memories.

458
00:26:53,879 --> 00:26:55,715
Oh, Sangenya.

459
00:26:57,383 --> 00:26:59,418
Are you still going to work?

460
00:26:59,485 --> 00:27:01,253
What are you doing here?

461
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,222
Well, I forgot my cell phone.

462
00:27:07,626 --> 00:27:10,896
Sangenya, is this something
you must do today--

463
00:27:10,963 --> 00:27:12,198
I must do it.

464
00:27:12,665 --> 00:27:14,300
Oh, I see.

465
00:27:14,867 --> 00:27:19,005
I would like you to take overtime
into consideration too.

466
00:27:22,808 --> 00:27:24,477
We are at work,

467
00:27:24,543 --> 00:27:27,246
so this may not be appropriate…

468
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:30,583
But Sangenya, you are my wife, right?

469
00:27:30,649 --> 00:27:35,654
As my wife, can you please
take into consideration my position,

470
00:27:36,322 --> 00:27:40,459
and my circumstances of being placed
in the middle of this mess?

471
00:27:40,526 --> 00:27:42,294
Want to go out for a drink once I'm done?

472
00:27:42,361 --> 00:27:44,296
What? Do you want to?

473
00:27:44,997 --> 00:27:46,932
I'll listen to my husband's
complaints then.

474
00:27:49,035 --> 00:27:52,204
Oh, in that case,

475
00:27:52,271 --> 00:27:55,941
I'll prepare for tomorrow as well.

476
00:27:59,945 --> 00:28:01,213
Husband and wife overtime.

477
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:19,965
Now, let's start the morning meeting.

478
00:28:20,032 --> 00:28:21,901
Kagimura is not here.

479
00:28:22,735 --> 00:28:26,105
Oh, so this day has finally come.
He's absent without notice.

480
00:28:26,172 --> 00:28:27,973
-I wonder if he's going to quit.
-Right.

481
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:29,942
Don't say such a thing.

482
00:28:30,009 --> 00:28:31,210
-I'm sorry.
-Sorry.

483
00:28:35,614 --> 00:28:40,653
Good morning, this is
Teiko Real Estate, Shinjuku office.

484
00:28:41,420 --> 00:28:43,956
Oh? Where are you now?

485
00:28:46,158 --> 00:28:48,060
Oh, you really went to that?

486
00:28:49,228 --> 00:28:51,530
Manager, Kagimura is on line one.

487
00:28:51,597 --> 00:28:52,932
See?

488
00:28:52,998 --> 00:28:55,067
He'll say, "I'm not coming in,
mental breakdown."

489
00:28:55,134 --> 00:28:56,335
Totally.

490
00:28:56,402 --> 00:28:57,503
This is Yashiro.

491
00:28:57,570 --> 00:29:02,007
Manager, I'm giving a tour of a property,
so I won't be at the morning meeting.

492
00:29:02,475 --> 00:29:05,478
Kagimura, is that true? Don't lie--

493
00:29:09,982 --> 00:29:13,052
This is wonderful.
It's like the South of France.

494
00:29:13,119 --> 00:29:14,854
Have you ever been to the South of France?

495
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:17,890
No, but it feels like it.

496
00:29:18,491 --> 00:29:20,826
This is cute.

497
00:29:20,893 --> 00:29:22,261
But this place…

498
00:29:24,330 --> 00:29:26,699
It's shaped strangely
so it'll be hard to place the furniture.

499
00:29:27,133 --> 00:29:30,002
We don't have any huge furniture.
It'll be fine.

500
00:29:30,069 --> 00:29:34,106
It's cheap and it could be bought
with what my dad is giving us.

501
00:29:34,406 --> 00:29:37,143
Kagimura. I like this place!

502
00:29:37,209 --> 00:29:40,646
In that case,
please sign the application form.

503
00:29:42,915 --> 00:29:44,183
I feel better now.

504
00:29:44,984 --> 00:29:46,152
I'm back.

505
00:29:46,218 --> 00:29:47,887
Welcome back.

506
00:29:48,787 --> 00:29:50,122
-Manager.
-Yes?

507
00:29:51,056 --> 00:29:52,525
I sold a property.

508
00:29:53,225 --> 00:29:54,293
What?

509
00:29:54,360 --> 00:29:56,695
The ¥43.8 million apartment in Toyosu

510
00:29:56,762 --> 00:29:58,998
was sold to Mr. and Mrs. Mitsushima.

511
00:29:59,064 --> 00:30:01,133
They were Chief Sangenya's clients,

512
00:30:01,700 --> 00:30:02,968
but I sold it to them.

513
00:30:06,005 --> 00:30:07,706
Sangenya, is it true?

514
00:30:07,973 --> 00:30:10,609
I don't know. I'm going out.

515
00:30:11,076 --> 00:30:14,914
It's true. As a proof, see?

516
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:16,081
Here's an application form.

517
00:30:17,116 --> 00:30:18,384
This is…

518
00:30:19,985 --> 00:30:22,221
a miracle!

519
00:30:23,088 --> 00:30:25,724
It's a miracle. It's a super miracle.

520
00:30:25,791 --> 00:30:27,826
It feels good to sell a house.

521
00:30:27,893 --> 00:30:31,497
Finding that out
is a huge step forward for you.

522
00:30:31,564 --> 00:30:33,566
Now, thank Niwano too.

523
00:30:34,266 --> 00:30:35,601
I haven't done anything.

524
00:30:36,035 --> 00:30:38,304
I know. I didn't learn anything
from Niwano.

525
00:30:40,139 --> 00:30:41,740
Toko, could you enter my sales?

526
00:30:42,074 --> 00:30:43,542
Got it.

527
00:31:03,362 --> 00:31:05,831
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

528
00:31:06,665 --> 00:31:07,933
Good work!

529
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:10,436
Be more formal.

530
00:31:10,502 --> 00:31:14,240
Niwano, good job!
The experienced one knows what's best.

531
00:31:14,673 --> 00:31:16,976
But I sold a property today.

532
00:31:17,042 --> 00:31:18,844
Mr. Niwano hasn't sold any property today.

533
00:31:20,613 --> 00:31:22,481
Kagimura!

534
00:31:22,548 --> 00:31:26,285
This is your very first one
since you started working here.

535
00:31:26,785 --> 00:31:30,489
Well, when you sell a home,
I feel more motivated as Sumo-kun too.

536
00:31:31,056 --> 00:31:33,492
Yeah! Unryu-style!

537
00:31:36,762 --> 00:31:39,198
-Self-centered.
-He's a shameless fellow.

538
00:31:39,565 --> 00:31:41,667
-Frivolous.
-That's it!

539
00:31:41,734 --> 00:31:43,936
-What does frivolous mean?
-I don't know.

540
00:31:44,003 --> 00:31:45,304
What's up with you?

541
00:31:45,371 --> 00:31:48,307
You all seem to be having fun
talking about me.

542
00:31:48,774 --> 00:31:51,443
Ms. Sangenya! What is this?

543
00:31:51,510 --> 00:31:54,413
I apologize. Kagimura, put it away!

544
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:55,648
Okay.

545
00:31:55,714 --> 00:31:57,049
Where is Ms. Sangenya?

546
00:31:57,116 --> 00:32:00,619
I'm Sangenya's boss, Yashiro.
Thank you for yesterday, Mr. Yamaji.

547
00:32:00,686 --> 00:32:01,754
Ms. Sangenya is not here?

548
00:32:01,820 --> 00:32:03,856
She is out right now.

549
00:32:03,922 --> 00:32:05,391
Then I'll ask you.

550
00:32:05,457 --> 00:32:07,259
Can't you control your employees
as a boss?

551
00:32:07,626 --> 00:32:10,496
-What?
-Everybody and everything is unorganized.

552
00:32:10,963 --> 00:32:13,766
I asked Ms. Sangenya to find a house
for my daughter,

553
00:32:13,832 --> 00:32:16,368
but then some random newbie
came out of nowhere

554
00:32:16,435 --> 00:32:19,471
and had my daughter sign a contract
without my permission.

555
00:32:19,772 --> 00:32:20,873
What is the meaning of this?

556
00:32:20,939 --> 00:32:23,075
-Ah…
-Don't say "Ah"!

557
00:32:24,009 --> 00:32:25,411
Oh.

558
00:32:25,477 --> 00:32:26,645
It was you, huh?

559
00:32:27,279 --> 00:32:29,615
You made my daughter sign the contract.

560
00:32:30,049 --> 00:32:31,283
Yes, I am.

561
00:32:31,350 --> 00:32:33,652
If she's going to live in Toyosu,
then I won't pay for it.

562
00:32:39,425 --> 00:32:40,993
Ah, goodbye.

563
00:32:41,060 --> 00:32:43,329
-Oh, I'm leaving too.
-Are you running away?

564
00:32:43,395 --> 00:32:45,297
Please come again tomorrow
regarding this matter.

565
00:32:45,364 --> 00:32:48,000
Ms. Sangenya will be here tomorrow.
See you.

566
00:32:48,334 --> 00:32:50,602
You are telling me to come again?
Who do you think you are?

567
00:32:50,669 --> 00:32:54,139
-What's going on with this company?
-I apologize,

568
00:32:54,206 --> 00:32:57,509
but the application form
your daughter filled out

569
00:32:57,576 --> 00:33:00,412
could be voided. So please don't worry.

570
00:33:04,483 --> 00:33:06,518
Is Shirasu skipping work without notice?

571
00:33:06,785 --> 00:33:10,989
I told her she would be fired
if she skipped work, so I might fire her.

572
00:33:11,056 --> 00:33:14,026
The younger generation
are messing things up everywhere.

573
00:33:14,093 --> 00:33:18,263
No, Mika Shirasu is not young.
She's over 30 now.

574
00:33:18,330 --> 00:33:20,199
Everyone under 40 is all the same.

575
00:33:20,265 --> 00:33:21,300
They are not motivated.

576
00:33:21,367 --> 00:33:25,871
There are some that are in their
20s and 30s that are motivated.

577
00:33:25,938 --> 00:33:28,841
Niwano here is in his 20s
but is very responsible,

578
00:33:28,907 --> 00:33:32,611
and knows what it means to work hard.
He's the minority though.

579
00:33:32,678 --> 00:33:34,279
I'm not so sure lately though.

580
00:33:34,546 --> 00:33:36,749
Well, but in general,

581
00:33:36,815 --> 00:33:39,718
compared to our generation,
they lack aggressiveness.

582
00:33:40,319 --> 00:33:43,655
I think you have to break your back
and work hard to gain some things.

583
00:33:44,256 --> 00:33:48,060
I guess that thinking itself is outdated.

584
00:33:48,127 --> 00:33:50,596
Why is society like this now?

585
00:33:51,864 --> 00:33:54,233
The factory I worked for never slept.

586
00:33:54,299 --> 00:33:57,269
The light was on 24 hours a day
and it was tough,

587
00:33:57,669 --> 00:33:59,538
but the employees were all united.

588
00:34:00,539 --> 00:34:04,810
Oh, you were part of the growth
of the company.

589
00:34:04,877 --> 00:34:07,146
No, I wasn't anything that impressive.

590
00:34:07,613 --> 00:34:12,217
What other joy is there
than working hard and earning money?

591
00:34:12,985 --> 00:34:15,821
When I was younger,
I only cared about work,

592
00:34:16,555 --> 00:34:18,924
and my first wife left me.

593
00:34:20,626 --> 00:34:22,861
I haven't done anything
for my wife either.

594
00:34:23,829 --> 00:34:26,932
As far as my daughter goes,
I'm just her wallet.

595
00:34:28,133 --> 00:34:29,334
But even so,

596
00:34:30,102 --> 00:34:32,704
I don't think I could have lived
any differently.

597
00:34:33,372 --> 00:34:34,940
-Niwano.
-Yes.

598
00:34:35,474 --> 00:34:39,044
Considering that you know the joy
of working hard, what's your opinion?

599
00:34:39,111 --> 00:34:40,245
My opinion?

600
00:34:40,312 --> 00:34:44,450
Are Yashiro and I fossils that's not
necessary for the future society?

601
00:34:45,884 --> 00:34:48,253
I understand both sides.

602
00:34:49,121 --> 00:34:51,423
I know that you have to work hard
in order to gain something.

603
00:34:52,024 --> 00:34:54,560
So I think I need to work harder.

604
00:34:55,694 --> 00:34:59,765
But if you're going to lose yourself
in the process of trying too hard,

605
00:35:00,332 --> 00:35:04,002
then I think it's fine to take time off
and enjoy life.

606
00:35:05,037 --> 00:35:08,841
So in other words,
I don't know the right answer.

607
00:35:09,141 --> 00:35:12,177
-What?
-No, you're honest.

608
00:35:13,145 --> 00:35:15,414
You understand society too.

609
00:35:16,181 --> 00:35:19,651
I'm sorry for being late.
My daughter has a fever.

610
00:35:19,718 --> 00:35:21,086
My mom had back pain

611
00:35:21,153 --> 00:35:23,822
and it took time to hand her
over to my ex.

612
00:35:23,889 --> 00:35:25,757
I didn't have time to call either.

613
00:35:25,824 --> 00:35:29,528
-Boy, you are trying hard too.
-What?

614
00:35:29,595 --> 00:35:32,931
When I know there are mothers
who are working hard like this,

615
00:35:32,998 --> 00:35:34,800
maybe this society is not so bad.

616
00:35:35,067 --> 00:35:38,170
-What?
-Where were you playing all alone?

617
00:35:38,237 --> 00:35:39,738
I wasn't alone.

618
00:35:39,805 --> 00:35:41,139
So you were playing!

619
00:35:41,206 --> 00:35:46,278
I wasn't playing, I was um… on a date.

620
00:35:47,479 --> 00:35:48,680
Oh my!

621
00:35:57,489 --> 00:35:58,557
Halt.

622
00:36:10,969 --> 00:36:12,137
What's the matter?

623
00:36:14,740 --> 00:36:17,409
You were very passionate during our match.

624
00:36:20,112 --> 00:36:22,848
Probably because tomorrow
is the day of the battle.

625
00:36:23,415 --> 00:36:24,550
Battle?

626
00:36:25,450 --> 00:36:26,585
Yes.

627
00:36:27,319 --> 00:36:29,021
Who are you going to battle with?

628
00:36:31,790 --> 00:36:32,958
With the person I love.

629
00:36:36,395 --> 00:36:37,963
Your love is…

630
00:36:38,630 --> 00:36:40,966
It's of course a woman, right?

631
00:36:42,467 --> 00:36:43,669
Yes.

632
00:36:58,116 --> 00:36:59,251
Welcome.

633
00:37:06,325 --> 00:37:07,593
I'll get them.

634
00:37:12,030 --> 00:37:13,098
How about you, Adachi?

635
00:37:13,665 --> 00:37:15,334
I don't have any appointments today.

636
00:37:15,901 --> 00:37:17,202
That's rare.

637
00:37:17,636 --> 00:37:18,804
I'll work harder.

638
00:37:20,038 --> 00:37:21,139
How about you, Sangenya?

639
00:37:21,206 --> 00:37:24,743
Today, I'll sell a property to
the Yamaji and Mitsushima couple.

640
00:37:25,010 --> 00:37:26,578
Those are my clients.

641
00:37:27,112 --> 00:37:29,781
Then you come too. Niwano, you come too!

642
00:37:30,515 --> 00:37:32,751
It's time, so I am going now!

643
00:37:33,251 --> 00:37:34,853
-Go!
-Yes!

644
00:37:38,657 --> 00:37:42,694
This is the perfect layout for a couple.

645
00:37:43,629 --> 00:37:47,199
It's barrier-free, so I think
it's great for the future too.

646
00:37:47,265 --> 00:37:48,734
-This is quite nice.
-Yes.

647
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,602
What is under here?

648
00:37:50,669 --> 00:37:52,638
Wait. What is this place?

649
00:37:52,704 --> 00:37:56,041
We told Kagimura that we'll buy
the condo in the Bay Area.

650
00:37:56,108 --> 00:37:59,011
Now, I'll show you downstairs.

651
00:38:01,747 --> 00:38:02,948
What?

652
00:38:05,117 --> 00:38:07,052
What is this place?

653
00:38:07,119 --> 00:38:10,722
A coffee shop? Oh, this is wonderful.

654
00:38:10,789 --> 00:38:12,157
I don't get it at all.

655
00:38:12,224 --> 00:38:15,527
Today, I am showing
Mr. Isao and Mrs. Akemi Yamaji

656
00:38:15,794 --> 00:38:18,530
a house they can consider moving into.

657
00:38:18,597 --> 00:38:19,965
For us to move into?

658
00:38:20,032 --> 00:38:21,600
So it's not our home?

659
00:38:21,933 --> 00:38:23,001
Right.

660
00:38:23,068 --> 00:38:26,471
Mr. and Mrs. Yamaji. I recommend
you sell your current house,

661
00:38:26,538 --> 00:38:29,841
and use the money
you were going to give your daughter

662
00:38:30,342 --> 00:38:33,612
to buy this property.

663
00:38:35,047 --> 00:38:36,481
What is she saying?

664
00:38:37,249 --> 00:38:38,550
Mr. Yamaji.

665
00:38:38,617 --> 00:38:43,155
Mr. and Mrs. Yamaji, I think you two
should think more about yourselves.

666
00:38:43,989 --> 00:38:48,126
You became adults
during the high-rate economic growth,

667
00:38:48,193 --> 00:38:52,798
and the idea that working hard is beauty
is in your core.

668
00:38:53,899 --> 00:38:55,867
Your wife suppressed her own feelings

669
00:38:55,934 --> 00:38:57,969
and lived a life as a subservient wife

670
00:38:58,036 --> 00:39:00,772
to support her husband.

671
00:39:01,540 --> 00:39:05,677
Mr. Yamaji worked from morning
to late night, 365 days a year,

672
00:39:05,744 --> 00:39:07,312
and went home just to sleep.

673
00:39:07,679 --> 00:39:10,382
He never saw the day his child was born,

674
00:39:10,449 --> 00:39:12,951
the first day she smiled,
or the first day she stood up,

675
00:39:13,385 --> 00:39:16,588
and just worked, worked and worked.

676
00:39:17,856 --> 00:39:22,027
However, since Mr. Yamaji's
generation worked hard,

677
00:39:22,094 --> 00:39:24,496
Japan really flourished.

678
00:39:24,930 --> 00:39:27,332
You already worked hard for the society,

679
00:39:27,399 --> 00:39:30,168
for the company, and for your family.

680
00:39:31,136 --> 00:39:33,371
It is not necessary for you to spend
your precious money

681
00:39:33,772 --> 00:39:36,942
on a younger generation
that only gives the bare minimum,

682
00:39:37,008 --> 00:39:39,377
tries to make a profit with little effort,

683
00:39:39,444 --> 00:39:42,013
and tries to suck everything
from their parents.

684
00:39:44,649 --> 00:39:47,552
Ms. Akemi, you said
you wanted to open a coffee shop

685
00:39:47,619 --> 00:39:51,656
-after Mr. Isao retired, right?
-Yes.

686
00:39:52,023 --> 00:39:55,427
Please give this shop as a gift
to your wife.

687
00:39:56,094 --> 00:39:59,898
We enjoyed those finger foods
you gave us the other day.

688
00:40:01,133 --> 00:40:03,368
I think it's a perfect item
for a coffee shop.

689
00:40:03,702 --> 00:40:05,003
I think it'll be popular.

690
00:40:06,304 --> 00:40:10,742
Mr. Isao, you are not that old
to completely retire.

691
00:40:12,144 --> 00:40:14,246
Please run a profitable coffee shop

692
00:40:14,312 --> 00:40:17,549
with your wife here.

693
00:40:19,484 --> 00:40:21,686
-That might be good.
-This is wonderful.

694
00:40:21,753 --> 00:40:23,288
Wait one second!

695
00:40:23,355 --> 00:40:26,758
If you buy this place,
then you can't buy us a house!

696
00:40:26,825 --> 00:40:30,195
That's right. You can't buy it.
You can't have them buy it for you!

697
00:40:30,262 --> 00:40:33,131
Dad! If you won't buy us a house,
then I'll sever my ties with you.

698
00:40:33,198 --> 00:40:36,168
Go ahead and cut off ties that are only
connected through money!

699
00:40:36,234 --> 00:40:39,471
Stop it! I didn't come here
to be lectured!

700
00:40:39,538 --> 00:40:40,906
Let's give up on the house.

701
00:40:41,506 --> 00:40:42,674
What are you saying?

702
00:40:43,308 --> 00:40:45,644
Having them pay millions,

703
00:40:45,710 --> 00:40:48,980
and signing a 35 year mortgage
is just too much for me to bear.

704
00:40:49,581 --> 00:40:51,249
I'll get sick from the pressure.

705
00:40:53,485 --> 00:40:56,755
Father, mother, don't worry about us,

706
00:40:57,656 --> 00:41:01,426
and please start a coffee shop
of your dreams.

707
00:41:02,894 --> 00:41:06,498
Yes, your daughter and her
husband are not relevant.

708
00:41:06,565 --> 00:41:08,967
Please live for yourselves.

709
00:41:09,034 --> 00:41:10,802
No, I don't like that!

710
00:41:11,336 --> 00:41:14,139
Don't worry. I will suggest
a place that is appropriate

711
00:41:14,206 --> 00:41:17,409
for the two of you,
Mr. and Mrs. Mitsushima.

712
00:41:20,779 --> 00:41:23,148
But first, Mr. Isao Yamaji,

713
00:41:23,215 --> 00:41:26,718
will you buy this house for ¥70 million?

714
00:41:29,154 --> 00:41:30,188
I'll buy it.

715
00:41:34,559 --> 00:41:35,760
I've got them.

716
00:41:36,795 --> 00:41:40,432
Wow, selling a house is incredible.

717
00:41:40,966 --> 00:41:42,901
Do you get it now?

718
00:41:44,069 --> 00:41:47,939
Kagimura, please have Mr. Yamaji
fill out the application form.

719
00:41:48,006 --> 00:41:51,276
Application form?
Does that mean it'll be my sales?

720
00:41:51,343 --> 00:41:52,577
That won't happen!

721
00:41:56,081 --> 00:41:58,984
Mr. and Mrs. Mitsushima, let's get going.

722
00:42:05,657 --> 00:42:08,760
Wait, this is a public housing complex.
I don't like it.

723
00:42:08,827 --> 00:42:10,896
-This is it.
-I'm leaving.

724
00:42:11,763 --> 00:42:14,499
Then Mr. Kentaro, please come.

725
00:42:22,974 --> 00:42:25,410
What is this? This hallway is uncool.

726
00:42:35,587 --> 00:42:38,223
What's going on here?

727
00:42:38,790 --> 00:42:41,059
It's like North Italy.

728
00:42:41,126 --> 00:42:43,295
Have you ever been to North Italy?

729
00:42:43,361 --> 00:42:45,697
No, but it feels like it.

730
00:42:46,932 --> 00:42:50,502
The storage space has been renovated
into an office with a desk.

731
00:42:55,640 --> 00:42:59,210
The partition that was once here
is being fully utilized as well.

732
00:43:05,283 --> 00:43:08,420
This complex was built 40 years ago,

733
00:43:08,486 --> 00:43:10,322
but it has a solid build.

734
00:43:10,989 --> 00:43:13,291
It's fully renovated,

735
00:43:13,358 --> 00:43:16,161
so the rooms feel spacious,

736
00:43:16,227 --> 00:43:21,066
and the property's green area
could be enjoyed as your own backyard.

737
00:43:21,666 --> 00:43:22,867
This is cool.

738
00:43:22,934 --> 00:43:24,135
It might be cool.

739
00:43:24,402 --> 00:43:26,271
This is cool.

740
00:43:26,972 --> 00:43:29,841
The cost is very reasonable

741
00:43:29,908 --> 00:43:33,611
-compared to the ones in the city.
-How much is it?

742
00:43:33,878 --> 00:43:35,647
It's ¥15 million.

743
00:43:35,714 --> 00:43:38,783
No way! Then I can buy it
without your father's support!

744
00:43:38,850 --> 00:43:40,251
It might be cool.

745
00:43:40,318 --> 00:43:43,855
This renovated public complex
is very popular among young couples.

746
00:43:43,922 --> 00:43:45,724
If we don't hurry, it'll sell.

747
00:43:46,224 --> 00:43:49,160
Your father is from a generation
where they worked hard

748
00:43:49,227 --> 00:43:51,696
all day every day,
to contribute to the growth of society.

749
00:43:51,763 --> 00:43:56,334
But it's not reasonable to think
that the economy will continue to boom.

750
00:43:56,768 --> 00:43:59,771
Mr. and Mrs. Mitsushima, you two
aren't from Mr. Yamaji's generation,

751
00:43:59,838 --> 00:44:03,742
who had to sacrifice time with his family
to work in a competitive working field.

752
00:44:03,808 --> 00:44:07,045
I would like to suggest that you enjoy
a modest, yet calm and happy life

753
00:44:07,112 --> 00:44:10,815
at this place. What do you think?

754
00:44:11,583 --> 00:44:14,152
Calm and happy life.

755
00:44:15,120 --> 00:44:17,288
That's it! That's what I want.

756
00:44:17,355 --> 00:44:19,858
Kenta! I think so too!

757
00:44:19,924 --> 00:44:22,594
Mr. Kentaro and Mrs. Hana Mitsushima,

758
00:44:22,660 --> 00:44:26,564
will you buy this home for ¥15 million?

759
00:44:29,334 --> 00:44:30,368
We'll take it.

760
00:44:31,603 --> 00:44:32,704
I've got them.

761
00:44:33,738 --> 00:44:36,107
Chief Sangenya sure is amazing.

762
00:44:36,908 --> 00:44:38,143
Hello.

763
00:44:39,644 --> 00:44:40,812
Mr. Rusudo!

764
00:44:41,346 --> 00:44:42,347
How do you know him?

765
00:44:42,647 --> 00:44:44,716
We met him at a bar the other day.

766
00:44:44,783 --> 00:44:46,951
We had a great time talking
about our hobbies.

767
00:44:47,018 --> 00:44:49,854
Why are you here though?

768
00:44:49,921 --> 00:44:52,023
Oh, I didn't mention it before

769
00:44:52,557 --> 00:44:56,561
but I'm a freelance realtor.

770
00:44:56,628 --> 00:44:57,996
No way!

771
00:44:59,497 --> 00:45:02,100
This property is nice, right?

772
00:45:02,801 --> 00:45:05,970
It's nice and bright.
It's well-ventilated too.

773
00:45:06,504 --> 00:45:08,540
It's a wonderful community.

774
00:45:08,606 --> 00:45:11,443
Yes, it is. She showed it to us.

775
00:45:12,243 --> 00:45:16,314
But do you know the number
of this property?

776
00:45:17,549 --> 00:45:18,683
What is it?

777
00:45:19,684 --> 00:45:22,520
-Oh, it's…
-It's 345.

778
00:45:24,456 --> 00:45:27,258
It's three, four, five.

779
00:45:28,726 --> 00:45:31,496
Three, four, five?

780
00:45:35,233 --> 00:45:37,936
Three, four, five?

781
00:45:38,336 --> 00:45:40,505
Miyoko?

782
00:45:41,239 --> 00:45:43,108
Miyoko? This place is Miyoko?

783
00:45:43,441 --> 00:45:46,611
Hana, I broke up with Miyoko
a long time ago.

784
00:45:46,678 --> 00:45:48,413
That's why I got married to you, Hana.

785
00:45:48,480 --> 00:45:51,082
No, this place is bad luck!

786
00:45:51,483 --> 00:45:53,518
He was two-timing me with Miyoko

787
00:45:53,585 --> 00:45:55,820
when we started dating.

788
00:45:55,887 --> 00:45:59,524
What's the point of talking about
something that happened so long ago?

789
00:45:59,591 --> 00:46:02,594
But Hana, this room is awesome!

790
00:46:02,660 --> 00:46:03,995
We can afford it too.

791
00:46:04,062 --> 00:46:06,698
No, I don't like it. No! No!

792
00:46:06,764 --> 00:46:08,233
Hana! Hana!

793
00:46:08,299 --> 00:46:11,469
That number 345 is following me
all the time!

794
00:46:11,536 --> 00:46:14,606
That number reminds me of Miyoko.

795
00:46:15,740 --> 00:46:19,177
Hana, history only moves forward.

796
00:46:19,244 --> 00:46:21,279
The past is the past.

797
00:46:21,346 --> 00:46:23,481
Yes, the past is the past.

798
00:46:23,815 --> 00:46:24,916
Don't worry.

799
00:46:25,283 --> 00:46:27,685
I have a property that's exactly
like that one.

800
00:46:29,220 --> 00:46:30,255
This way.

801
00:46:32,557 --> 00:46:34,025
This is it.

802
00:46:35,026 --> 00:46:36,027
Oh! It's 830!

803
00:46:36,094 --> 00:46:37,328
It's Yazawa!

804
00:46:37,595 --> 00:46:40,765
-Yes, it's Yazawa.
-Yazawa?

805
00:46:41,032 --> 00:46:44,502
Are you an idiot? Yazawa could only
be Eikichi Yazawa!

806
00:46:44,569 --> 00:46:48,940
He's a rock star that represents Japan!
Eight, three, zero

807
00:46:49,007 --> 00:46:51,209
means Yazawa!

808
00:46:51,276 --> 00:46:54,212
For us, eight, three, zero
is our lucky number!

809
00:46:54,546 --> 00:46:55,847
That's right.

810
00:47:01,719 --> 00:47:03,254
I just got it done.

811
00:47:03,521 --> 00:47:04,556
Thank you.

812
00:47:05,290 --> 00:47:06,958
I'll be going now.

813
00:47:09,194 --> 00:47:10,628
Ms. Shirasu?

814
00:47:10,695 --> 00:47:12,297
Please, take a look inside too.

815
00:47:12,897 --> 00:47:16,067
Ms. Shirasu! What are you doing here?

816
00:47:16,134 --> 00:47:19,070
I can't say no
when an attractive guy asks for a favor.

817
00:47:19,370 --> 00:47:20,605
You betrayed us?

818
00:47:20,672 --> 00:47:24,175
I don't know. I don't work
for Teiko Real Estate.

819
00:47:24,909 --> 00:47:26,411
Hey!

820
00:47:34,919 --> 00:47:37,355
-Oh cool!
-These are all rare items!

821
00:47:38,156 --> 00:47:41,893
It's all Ei-chan! Ei-chan!

822
00:47:42,860 --> 00:47:46,898
Kenta! I definitely want this one!

823
00:47:46,965 --> 00:47:48,366
-Then let's take this one!
-Yes.

824
00:47:48,866 --> 00:47:52,270
Then could you fill out this
application form?

825
00:47:52,337 --> 00:47:53,371
Yes.

826
00:48:11,089 --> 00:48:12,323
I lost…

827
00:48:32,010 --> 00:48:35,280
Chief Sangenya, you have a plan
for a comeback like usual?

828
00:48:35,713 --> 00:48:38,716
This isn't it, right? There's more, right?

829
00:48:46,824 --> 00:48:48,092
No.

830
00:49:03,541 --> 00:49:06,010
-Manager!
-What?

831
00:49:06,978 --> 00:49:10,748
Chief Sangenya lost to that Kenji Rusudo!

832
00:49:13,451 --> 00:49:15,653
After selling a home
to Mr. and Mrs. Yamaji,

833
00:49:15,720 --> 00:49:17,655
she tried to sell a place
to Mr. and Mrs. Mitsushima,

834
00:49:17,722 --> 00:49:19,724
but Rusudo stole them.

835
00:49:19,791 --> 00:49:21,359
Calm down, Niwano.

836
00:49:21,426 --> 00:49:24,295
So first, she sold a house
to Mr. and Mrs. Yamaji, right?

837
00:49:24,362 --> 00:49:27,065
But Mr. Yamaji wasn't planning
to buy a house for himself, right?

838
00:49:27,131 --> 00:49:29,734
Even so, she sold it. A house
with a coffee shop downstairs.

839
00:49:29,801 --> 00:49:31,269
Oh, I see.

840
00:49:31,336 --> 00:49:34,372
Then, you guys went to show a property
to Mr. and Mrs. Mitsushima?

841
00:49:34,839 --> 00:49:38,376
Yes, then Kenji Rusudo suddenly appeared

842
00:49:39,210 --> 00:49:41,779
and instantly captured
Mr. and Mrs. Mitsushima's heart.

843
00:49:42,613 --> 00:49:44,082
Chief Sangenya was just standing there.

844
00:49:46,718 --> 00:49:47,819
Kenji…

845
00:49:49,754 --> 00:49:52,724
Who is that Kenji Rusudo?

846
00:49:54,359 --> 00:49:56,661
He's truly terrifying.

847
00:49:58,529 --> 00:50:00,431
Kenji Rusudo…

848
00:50:04,635 --> 00:50:07,171
Kenji Rusudo…

849
00:50:11,609 --> 00:50:14,679
Jin-ken-do-su…

850
00:50:15,813 --> 00:50:16,881
ru…

851
00:50:21,619 --> 00:50:22,720
I'll be using my paid vacation

852
00:50:22,787 --> 00:50:24,489
-for a while.
-Let's follow her.

853
00:50:24,555 --> 00:50:26,290
We'll find out about their relationship.

854
00:50:26,357 --> 00:50:28,259
-You used me?
-Sorry.

855
00:50:28,526 --> 00:50:31,095
-That's Manchichi. How memorable.
-Manchichi?

856
00:50:31,162 --> 00:50:33,030
I want a home that looks good
on the outside.

857
00:50:33,097 --> 00:50:33,998
BEAUTY AND THE BEAST COUPLE
GOES HOUSE HUNTING

858
00:50:34,065 --> 00:50:36,100
-Who are you?
-I had makeup on.

859
00:50:36,167 --> 00:50:38,469
There's no point unless I marry a beauty.
Our engagement is off.

860
00:50:38,536 --> 00:50:39,537
I'm Manchichi!

861
00:50:39,604 --> 00:50:41,906
You two are similar in that
you care only about the exterior.

862
00:50:41,973 --> 00:50:43,441
I'll fix your relationship.

863
00:50:43,508 --> 00:50:45,576
And I'll sell you a house!

864
00:50:45,643 --> 00:50:48,112
You're the man that stole
two sales from me.

865
00:50:48,179 --> 00:50:50,481
I still love you.
